<content type="application/x.deki0805+xml" title="script"><body xmlns:eval="http://mindtouch.com/2007/dekiscript"><div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div> <p>Much like the HTML <code>script</code> element, this is used to declare a script to be used by the XUL window. You should usually put scripts in a separate file pointed to by the <span class="script">template.XULAttr("src")</span> attribute, but you may also place the script inline inside the opening and closing <code>script</code> tags. </p><p>More information is available in the <a href="en/XUL_Tutorial/Adding_Event_Handlers">XUL tutorial</a>.
</p>
<dl><dt> Attributes
</dt><dd> <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "script.src", "src")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "script.type", "type")</span>
</dd></dl>
<h3 name="Examples"> Examples </h3>
<pre>
 &lt;script src="test.js"/&gt;
 &lt;script src="http://example.com/js/test.js"/&gt;
 &lt;script&gt;
   function foo(){
     // code
    }
  &lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
<h3 name="Attributes"> Attributes </h3>
<p><span class="script">template.XULAttrInc("script.src")</span>
<span class="script">template.XULAttrInc("script.type")</span>
